<h2>Absorbed Dose</h2>

<p><strong>Absorbed dose</strong>&nbsp;describes the amount of energy&nbsp;=
deposited per unit mass in an object or person. The units for absorbed dose=
 are gray&nbsp;(Gy, international unit) and rad (rad, U.S. unit).&nbsp;&nbs=
p;</p>



